quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  109,1,"Say: &quot;O disbelievers!&quot;"
  109,2,"&quot;I worship not that which you worship.&quot;"
  109,3,"&quot;Nor will you worship whom I worship.&quot;"
  109,4,"&quot;And I shall not worship that which you are worshipping.&quot;"
  109,5,"&quot;Nor will you worship that which I worship.&quot;"
  109,6,"&quot;To you be your religion, and to me my religion.&quot;"
  110,1,"When there comes the help of Allah and the Conquest."
  110,2,"And you see that the people enter Allah's religion in crowds."
  110,3,"So, glorify the praises of your Lord, and ask His forgiveness. Verily, He is the One Who accepts the repentance and Who forgives."
  111,1,"Perish the two hands of Abu Lahab and perish he!"
  111,2,"His wealth and his children will not benefit him!"
  111,3,"He will enter a Fire full of flames!"
  111,4,"And his wife too, who carries wood."
  111,5,"In her neck is a twisted rope of Masad."
